      • onRecordSnapshotError

        void onRecordSnapshotError(java.lang.String recordName,
                         DeepstreamException deepstreamException)
        Called if an error occured while getting the record data. The most likely error case is Event.RECORD_NOT_FOUND if the record doesn't exist, followed by Event.MESSAGE_DENIED, although it could also be a storage failure such as Event.STORAGE_RETRIEVAL_TIMEOUT or Event.CACHE_RETRIEVAL_TIMEOUT
        Parameters:
        recordName - The name of the record that has been found
        deepstreamException - The DeepstreamException thrown
